Tobi Aworinde Transcorp Hilton Abuja has attributed its success in the hospitality industry to the hard work and commitment of its staff and loyalty of its customers. The General Manager of the hotel, Kevin Brett, said this as the hotel received four awards, including Africa’s Leading Business Hotel for the sixth consecutive year at the 27th annual World Travel Awards. The WTA was established in 1993 to acknowledge, reward and celebrate excellence across all key sectors of the travel, tourism and hospitality industries. According to a statement, Transform Hilton Abuja, which is owned by Transcorp Hotels Plc, the hospitality subsidiary of Transnational Corporation of Nigeria Plc, also won the awards for Nigeria’s Leading Hotel, Nigeria’s Leading Business Hotel and Nigeria’s Leading Hotel Suite (the Presidential Suite). Brett said, “We are delighted once again to receive the World Travel Awards in various categories. It is a testament to the fact that the hard work and commitment our team put in daily is recognised and appreciated. The Managing Director, Transcorp Hotels Plc, Dupe Olusola, in her remarks, was quoted as highlighting the significance of receiving such an award during the COVID-19 pandemic. Olusola said, “It is such a pleasure to receive the ultimate seal of excellence in the global tourism and hospitality industry from the World Travel Awards. At a time where travellers are exploring only the best hospitality products, the significance of this recognition is truly important.” Copyright PUNCH.
